==English==

===Verb===
{{en-verb|head=[[hang]] [[on]]|hangs on|hanging on|hung on}}

# {{context|idiomatic}} To [[wait]] a [[moment]] (usually imperative).
#: '''''Hang on'''. Let me check.''
# To [[hold]], [[grasp]], or [[grip]].
#: '''''Hang on''' to the handle so you don't drop it.''
# {{context|idiomatic}} To keep; to store something for someone
#: '''''Hang on''' to my jacket until I get back.''
# {{context|idiomatic}} To pay close [[attention]].
#: ''The audience '''hangs on''' his every word.''
# {{context|idiomatic}} To continually [[believe]] in something; to have [[faith]] in.
#: ''He's got a philosophy he '''hangs on''' to.''
# {{context|idiomatic}} To [[persevere]].
#: ''Just '''hang on''' and keep going; this pain won't last forever.''

